They've got one thing on the menu, with a few variations. They do that thing very well. There's meat burek (ground beef), cheese burek and spinach burek. Delicious pies of hot, crispy phyllo with your choice of filling come fresh out of the oven. A slice is a quarter of pie of about 14-15" diameter and costs $4.50. This would be a meal for most people. What's not to love about this place.

This family owned spot is "mama's cooking" at its purest form. The owner and chef is a down to earth purist who put a her special touch into every pie she bakes. Think "cheese/spinach/meat/ quiche" and top off with your favorite sauce or dressing. I can see this place getting turned into a franchise by some shrewd businessman but for now, it's Pelham Parkways/Morris Park's true hidden diamond in the rough.
